						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1422 (1500 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>States that Kandāḍai Mādhavayyaṅgār, a disciple of Kandāḍai Rāmānujayyaṅgār, the <hi rend="italic">dharmakartā</hi> of the <hi rend="italic">Rāmānujakūṭam</hi> at Tiruvaraṅgam—Tirupati, constructed a temple to the north of the Nānmugaṉ-gōpuram and conssecrated therein the images of Viṭṭhalēśvara and Madhurakavi-Āḻvār and arranged for their worship and also constructed a kitchen. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1422</hi> expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="italic">Rudravandyē,</hi> <hi rend="bold">Raudri, Makara, śu. 10, Monday, Rōhiṇi</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1500, December 30, ·25; f.d.n. ·87, the week day was, however, Wednesday, not Monday.</hi> Sōma in the text is obviously a mistake for Saumya.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
